Privacy Policy
1. Information Collection and Use
Our app collects and uses various types of information to provide its services. The information we collect can be categorized into the following:

User-provided information: When you create an account, we collect your email address, password, and other profile information you choose to provide.
Usage data: We collect information about how you use our app, including your interactions with our content generation and scheduling features.
Social media data: When you connect your social media accounts, we collect information about your social media profiles and activity.
Analytics data: We use Firebase Analytics to collect data about your app usage, including metrics such as screen views, button clicks, and other interactions.
We use this information to:

Provide and improve our app's features and services
Personalize your experience across the app
Analyze usage patterns to enhance our app's functionality and user experience
2. Data Storage and Security
We store user data using Firebase Firestore, a secure and reliable NoSQL database. We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data, including:

Encryption in transit using HTTPS
Authentication and authorization mechanisms to control access to user data
Regular security audits and monitoring
We retain user data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide our services. When you delete your account, we will delete your personal data within a reasonable timeframe.

3. User Rights and Choices
You have the right to:

Access your personal information by logging into your account
Update your personal information through your account settings
Request deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us at support@socialmedia-manager.app
Opt-out of certain data collection practices, such as analytics, through your device settings
To exercise these rights, please contact us at support@socialmedia-manager.app. We will respond to your request within 30 days.

4. Third-Party Services
Our app uses the following third-party services:

OpenRouter API: We use OpenRouter to provide AI-powered content generation and analysis. When you use these features, your input data is sent to OpenRouter's servers for processing. Please review OpenRouter's privacy policy for more information.
Firebase Services: We use Firebase for authentication, data storage, and analytics. Firebase collects certain data as described in their privacy policy.
Social Media APIs: When you connect your social media accounts, we collect information from these platforms through their APIs. Please review the privacy policies of the respective social media platforms for more information.
5. Contact Information
For any privacy-related inquiries or requests, please contact us at support@socialmedia-manager.app.
